The mainstream of the Yangtze River has achieved full coverage of water green comprehensive service areas-Xinhua News Agency.
Xinhua News Agency, Wuhan, December 11 (Reporter Wang Xian): The Fuling Water-based Green Comprehensive Service Area in Chongqing City was completed and put into operation as scheduled on the 10th, which is the second Water-based Green Comprehensive Service Area officially put into operation in the upper reaches of the Yangtze River following the Luzhou Water-based Green Comprehensive Service Area which was officially put into operation on the 8th.
Up to this point, the Waterborne Green Comprehensive Service Zone has now covered the upper, middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River.
Minister of Transport Jiang Hao Administration Vice Minister Qiu Jianhua introduced that previously, Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, Anhui, Jiangsu and other provinces have already built 10 water green comprehensive service areas in the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze, which have been recognized by a wide range of crewmembers and has played an important role in promoting the high-quality development of the Yangtze shipping.
The full coverage of the integrated green service zone over water is another milestone event in the construction of the “Green Shipping Initiative on the Yangtze River”, significantly enhancing the capability for receiving marine pollutants as well as providing shipping services.
According to the introduction, the water-based green comprehensive service area is an important facility that provides comprehensive production and living services to ships and crews, as well as helps solve their "emergency distress" problems.
This time two water green integrated service areas constructed and operated in the upper reaches of the Yangtze River integrate living services, production services and government services, taking green and environmental protection as the theme, with ship repairs and ship emergency rescue services as features, to realize the "one-time berthing and multiple services" for vessels in the harbor, which will make the working and life more efficient and convenient for the crews sailing along the Yangtze River all year round.
